@giorgioarmani built the blueprint for the power blazer. ARMANI/Archivio brings it back into focus.
Marking 50 years of the house, the project reworks the archive with a modern lens. The latest drop revisits 13 looks from 1979 to 1994, reproduced with precision and released for the first time.
At the centre is the jacket, fluid, exact, and quietly subversive. The silhouettes that reshaped tailoring still feel effortless now. More April Fashion news at the link in bio.

KL Rahul (@klrahul) steps into a new fashion chapter with Paul & Shark (@paulandshark), co-creating a Spring/Summer 2026 capsule that blends understated elegance with performance. Rooted in Italian craftsmanship and layered with subtle Indian influences, the collection reimagines classics through a modern, travel-ready lens. Lightweight textures, refined silhouettes, and a palette of soft neutrals accented with blue and brick red define the offering. It’s a study in quiet luxury, where style feels considered, never overstated.
